StoryAsset.name: Short Post Match Cup Leg 1 of 2 Qualifying

keyValuePair.Value: Can you still go through?
It was a narrow defeat and leaves you in with a chance of overturning the deficit in the second leg. Can %1s get through? What will you need to do in the return leg at home now?
We've got a great chance of progressing.

We weren't at our best today but we didn't fold. That defeat is disappointing but we're still in with a great chance of going through. We'll be more aggressive in the home leg and we'll have a packed stadium roaring us on.
It wasn't easy for us, was it?

%1s put us under a lot of pressure. They're a good team. We never got into our rhythm and that made it a difficult game us. We spent a lot of time chasing the ball. But it's still all to play for. I'm sure we can create chances in the second leg. We'll give it a go.
They had all the possession.

The opposition were very strong in possession and found ways to play round too often for my liking. I think our boys got taught a bit of a lesson. But they can improve. They'll have to if we're going to make home advantage count in the second leg.
How tough will it be to come back from that defeat?
You would have hoped to take an advantage away for the second leg. Instead, your %1s side slipped to a defeat at home today. Can you overturn the deficit? How will you approach the next game now?
We have to believe in ourselves.
I don't think there's much between the two sides. We can be better than we were today. We have to believe we can go and get a result away from home now. Yes, I think we can still go through.
We've still got a chance.

%1s were very good defensively today and then they hit us on the break. I believe we have the quality going forward to do something similar in the second leg. I trust the boys to come up with the goods. We're still in with a chance.
We couldn't cope defensively.

We thought we were set up well to cope with their attacking players today. But they dominated us in key areas. We didn't cope defensively. Our boys were second to the loose balls and gave possession away too easily. We'll have to improve in the second leg if we're going to get through.
Has your chance gone now after that defeat?
Such a crushing defeat in the home leg, you can't expect to progress in the competition now, can you? What went wrong today? And how will you approach the return game?
We've still got pride to play for.

Our lads worked hard but couldn't get the better of the opposition and we were sloppy when they had the ball. They have players who we knew could hurt us. And they did. Now we have to go into the second leg playing for pride. We owe our fans a performance, don't we?
We have to keep believing.

We came up short in all the one-on-one battles and we never got into the game as an attacking force at all. It was a bad night for us but we have to keep believing. Away to %1s, if we get the first goal, who knows what could happen?
We have to be realistic, don't we?

We pride ourselves on %1s being a team that never gives up. But that was a terrible display and we have to be realistic about our chances. We'll give it everything, though. If nothing else, I don't want a repeat of this performance in the second leg.
Is that your chance in the competition gone?
That was a pretty heavy defeat. How do you explain what went wrong? Do you think your chance in the %1s has gone now, even with the home leg to play?
We'll need to get the first goal.

We'll need to start quickly and get hold of the game early on in the second leg. And we'll have to cut out the basic defensive errors. But we'll give it a go. If we get the first goal in the next game, who knows what could happen?
We need to be better all over the pitch.

Look, %1s are a decent outfit and we definitely came off second-best here. We didn't get enough of the ball to threaten as an attacking force at all. We need to put in better performances all over the pitch in the return leg and we'll need a bit of luck. But we won't give up, I can promise you that.
It'll be tough now.

That wasn't a %1s performance today. We've given ourselves a mountain to climb if we want to go through now. But we'll prepare properly and hope we can get the first goal in the second leg at home. Who knows what might happen when we have our fans behind us?
A useful score draw. Are you favourites now?
Are your %1s side favourites to go through now? A score draw away from home is a decent result. Will you approach the home leg in a different way to today's game?
It could have been even better.

I couldn't have asked for much more from my players and, if we'd been better defensively, we could have been in an even stronger position. But it's not a bad result and I'll be disappointed if we don't get the win at home now to go through.
We'll have to take our chances.
We'll have to take our chances.

It was a good result, even though one or two individual performances weren't up to our usual standard. If we can make sure we have more of the possession in the second leg, I hope we can finish the job. You won't hear me calling us favourites, though!

It was a good result, even though one or two individual performances weren't up to our usual standard. If we can make sure we have more of the possession in the second leg, I hope we can finish the job. You won't hear me calling us favourites, though!
I think we're the better team.
We've put ourselves in a very good position. I'd have been happier with a win but we did the job here. Now, with our home crowd behind us, we have to prove we deserve to go through to the next round.
Are you in a good position now?
A draw for %1s today. And a clean sheet. Do you think the hard work is done? How will you approach the second leg at home now?
The clean sheet was vital.

I'm very happy with how we performed defensively. Everybody stuck to the task. To come away and keep a clean sheet here is a great achievement. And it gives us a chance now to finish the job in front of our own fans.
We'll make chances at home.

The boys didn't have a lot of the ball in good positions and we didn't make the most of the couple of opportunities that came our way. But a draw here certainly isn't a bad result. I'm sure we can make chances at home. We'll have to get players in the box and make sure we're ruthless in front of goal.
Let's give our fans something to celebrate.

This is a tough place to come and we're very happy with a goalless draw. Now we have to be ready to finish the job at home. I believe in these players. They're a very determined bunch. I'm optimistic we can give our fans something to celebrate in the second leg.
Could that prove to be a costly draw?
You must have wanted to take an advantage with you into the second leg. Instead, the draw means you're probably second favourites to go through. How do you plan to approach the away game now?
We'll have to keep things tight.

We were poor defensively today and that meant we had to endure a pretty tough 90 minutes. But we're still in it. The lads know we'll have to improve in the key areas of the pitch. But look, we'll go into the away leg determined to win.
We're still in this, for sure.
We're still in this, for sure.

I expected more from the lads in this first leg, but I still believe we've got good enough attacking players to put things right away from home. We're disappointed with the draw and know we didn't do ourselves justice. But it's not over. We're still in this tie.

I expected more from the lads in this first leg, but I still believe we've got good enough attacking players to put things right away from home. We're disappointed with the draw and know we didn't do ourselves justice. But it's not over. We're still in this tie.
A draw wasn't the result we were looking for.

Of course we're frustrated not to be taking a lead into the second leg. I didn't think we looked up to the challenge. But it just means the away game is a one-off now, a knock-out tie. If we go into it with a positive attitude, I believe we can still go through.
A frustrating game for you. Can you still go through?
I'd guess you believe %1s should always win home games. But you've been held to a goalless draw here. What will you need to improve if you're going to win away from home and go through?
We'll need another clean sheet.

We worked really hard for the clean sheet today and I think that gives us hope. We've got to treat the away game as a mini-final now. Let's give nothing away and try to find a bit of quality when it counts. Whoever wins will go through and I believe that can be us.
We paid for missing chances.

I thought we played pretty well and probably should have won. It was a pity we couldn't make the most of the opportunities we created. The opposition will come at us on their own ground, though. Maybe our boys will have a little more room and will be able to make their quality count in the second leg.
We always expect to score.

We go into every game hoping to win and, definitely, expecting to score. This first leg didn't go to plan but a goalless draw isn't the worst result in the world. The clean sheet gives us hope and we'll go to the away game believing we can get through.
That was an impressive display, wasn't it?
To come away and win by such a handsome margin! You must be delighted. %1s look as if they're as good as through already. How will you approach the second leg now?
We'll try to be even better in the second leg.

We've put ourselves in a very strong position. We were very determined to stick together when we didn't have the ball here. I think if we can start well and the lads take a grip on the game at home, we might be ready to give our fans a performance to remember.
I'm proud of the performance.

I have to give all the credit to the players. It's up to them to go out and do the job and we've put ourselves in a great position. If we can be disciplined again defensively in the second leg, and snuff out any hopes the opposition might have, I'm confident we'll go through.
We'll be professional in the home leg.

Yes, we put on a great display here. You have to say we've given ourselves every chance to progress. But I want us to maintain our standards. Let's be professional and give our own fans a game to remember at home now.
Could you have won by more?
You must pleased. %1s's win is a big step towards the next round. Could it have been more convincing? What do you do now: go for more goals in the away leg or hang onto what you've got?
The tie's not over yet.

We did really well today and I'm very happy with the win. But let's not pretend we're through yet. It's still evenly balanced. They're a good side and we'll have to be at our best again in the second leg.
The lads have put down a marker.

We were excellent today. I thought the boys controlled the tempo of the game. We've put down a marker but we know we're not through yet. We have the advantage, of course, but we'll need to dominate again if we're going to get another positive result in the second leg.
I'll trust us to finish the job.

It was a pretty narrow win, to be honest. I hoped for more goals. I can't say I was delighted with the performance but at least we looked pretty steady defensively. I'll talk to the lads tomorrow. They'll have to be at their very best away from home now if we're going to get through.
That was the perfect result, wasn't it?
It's always a great atmosphere when your %1s boys are at home. And the crowd enjoyed tonight. A big win. Did you enjoy the game, too? Have you done enough now to progress?
We need the right attitude.

It was a great performance from the boys. We were outstanding at the back and limited their chances and we had great energy in midfield. I want us to go into the second leg with the same attitude now. If we do that, we'll go through.
A great display all round.

We were fantastic. The win was all about our attacking play. We ripped the opposition to pieces at times. Now it's up to us to be resilient and brave. We'll be under more pressure in the away leg and we'll need to defend well to make sure we go through without any scares.
You can never tell in football.

Of course we're very happy with the win and happy we got the goals to put us in such a good position. But we know we'll need to focus in the second leg. If the opposition were to get an early goal, who knows what might happen?
Can your boys finish the job now?
You couldn't have asked for much more from your boys than to win the away leg. At home now, with the crowd behind you, are you pretty confident you can finish the job?
There's only one goal in it.
Of course I'm happy with how well we played and I thought we deserved to win. But there's still only a goal in it. We'll have to be at our best again if we want to make sure we go through.
Let's hope we're as good in the second leg.

It's too early to be thinking that we've already done the hard work. Our fans will expect us to win the home leg, of course. The players stood up really strong in this first leg. We'll need the same again from them all to make sure we go through.
Of course we have the advantage.

Some of our football was absolutely top-class today. The boys gave us everything and that determination earned us the win. But they know they'll be in for another tricky game in the second leg. If the opposition were to score first at our place, who knows what could happen?

Some of our football was absolutely top-class today. The boys gave us everything and that determination earned us the win. But they know they'll be in for another tricky game in the second leg. If the opposition were to score first at our place, who knows what could happen?
Did you grab a decisive advantage today?

%1s winning the away leg by a two-goal margin must give your boys the advantage. The crowd will be roaring you on in the second leg. Do you think you've already done enough to be sure of going through?
I think we can be even better.
Of course we've put ourselves in a very good position. That was a great win. But we'll have to make sure in the next game. I don't want our supporters to have too many scares at our place!
We'll need another strong performance.

We won tonight because we played at our absolute maximum. The boys dominated possession and didn't give up any chances at all that I can remember. I trust them to be just as professional in the home leg. As long as we keep a clean sheet we'll go through now.
We need more of the same!

We've put ourselves in a very strong position. We were super-competitive and won all our battles here. I hope that's set the standard for us. If we're as good in there in the home leg, I'm confident we'll go through. I want our supporters to enjoy the game!

We've put ourselves in a very strong position. We were super-competitive and won all our battles here. I hope that's set the standard for us. If we're as good in there in the home leg, I'm confident we'll go through. I want our supporters to enjoy the game!
Does a two-goal advantage give you the edge now?

It was a tough game but your boys put some daylight between %1s and the opposition. Does a two-goal advantage make all the difference? Are you confident now you can go away and finish the job in the second leg?
It's only half-time in the tie.

We know we've got ourselves into a very good position. The extra goal was a real bonus. But the job's not done yet. The second leg could go either way now and the opposition will feel that, if they get one back, the tie will be open again.
That's the commitment I want.

Of course the two-goal margin is a big plus for us. We stayed strong as a unit and limited them to very few chances. I believe in our boys, if they're as determined and organised again away from home, I'm pretty sure we'll have enough to go through.
We could have scored more.

The boys did well today up to a point. Yes, we've got a two-goal lead to take into the return fixture. But we could have scored more. We should have put the tie out of sight. The lads will have to go for it again in the second leg. Let's get a goal or two to finish the job!

The boys did well today up to a point. Yes, we've got a two-goal lead to take into the return fixture. But we could have scored more. We should have put the tie out of sight. The lads will have to go for it again in the second leg. Let's get a goal or two to finish the job!
